# Domain Driven Design

Every business concept belongs to a bounded context.

Always identify:

- Entities
- Value Objects
- Aggregates
- Domain Services
- Domain Events
- Repositories

---

# Entities

Entities own identity.

Never compare entities only by value.

---

# Value Objects

Value Objects are immutable.

Prefer Value Objects whenever identity is unnecessary.

---

# Aggregates

Protect business consistency.

Only Aggregate Roots may be modified externally.

---

# Domain Services

Use only when business logic cannot naturally belong to an Entity or Value Object.

---

# Domain Events

Use events to communicate between bounded contexts.

Avoid direct coupling.

---

# Repository

Repositories expose aggregate persistence.

Business logic never belongs inside repositories.